<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,1454,2056]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,200,1454,1480]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Trees</emphasis>
, branches glabrous, inermous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[581,676,1454,1480]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Nectary</emphasis>
absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[784,879,1454,1480]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Stipules</emphasis>
caducous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1020,1102,1454,1480]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Leaves</emphasis>
imparipinnate, 5–6–foliolate, leaflets alternate, ovate-elliptic, venation brochidodromous, translucid punctuation absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1193,1351,1490,1516]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Inflorescence</emphasis>
raceme, terminal. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[247,342,1526,1552]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Flowers</emphasis>
pedicellate, zygomorphic, diplostemonous; calyx gamosepalous, sepals 5, corolla dialypetalous, papilionaceous, lilac, petals 5; androecium monadelphous, homodinamous, anthers longitudinal; ovary superior, stipitate, pauciovulate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[402,464,1598,1624]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Fruit</emphasis>
legume, sessile, oblanceolate, plane, margin straight, epicarp glabrous, brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1384,1451,1598,1624]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Seeds</emphasis>
orbicular, plane, coat black, hilum basal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
